Class CollectorTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.SwingWorker<java.lang.Void,java.lang.Void>
      • uk.ac.cam.darknet.gui.CollectorTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, java.util.concurrent.Future<java.lang.Void>, java.util.concurrent.RunnableFuture<java.lang.Void>

    public class CollectorTask
extends javax.swing.SwingWorker<java.lang.Void,java.lang.Void>
    A SwingWorker task that runs a Secondary Data Collector. It is used to notify the GUI that the given collector has finished executing its task so that the GUI can display nice progress bar but still be responsive.
    Author:
    Augustin Zidek
